# MCP Module

{{ project_name }} includes [Model Context Protocol (MCP)](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/) integration for AI tool usage.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Start the MCP server
pnpm --filter mcp start
```

## Available Tools

The MCP server exposes the following tools:

| Tool | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `echo` | Echo back input text |
| `timestamp` | Get current timestamp |
| `http_fetch` | Fetch data from HTTP endpoints |

## Configuration

Configure the MCP server in `mcp/src/config.ts`:

```typescript
export const config = {
  name: '{{ project_name }}-mcp',
  version: '1.0.0',
};
```

## Integration

### Claude Desktop

Add to your Claude Desktop config:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "{{ project_slug }}": {
      "command": "pnpm",
      "args": ["--filter", "mcp", "start"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Testing

```bash
# Run MCP tests
pnpm --filter mcp test
```

